President Obama authorized a successful operation to rescue American citizen Jessica Buchanan, who had been held hostage in Somalia for three months. The operation was carried out by Special Operations Forces, and Buchanan is now on her way home. The President expressed his pride in the troops involved in the mission and thanked the professionals who supported their efforts. He condemned the criminals and pirates who kidnapped Buchanan and emphasized that the United States will not tolerate the abduction of its citizens. The President assured that every effort will be made to secure the safety of American citizens and bring their captors to justice, sending a message that the US will stand strongly against any threats to its people.